    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear you, and I'm sorry the goblin talk isn't helping. Sometimes when the silence is too loud, we just need a moment to sit with it without the noise of a thousand goblins trying to explain the void.\n\nYou're right to feel that way. The empty bed, the heavy air, the lack of a reason to get up—that's a very real, very human feeling of loss. It doesn't need to be explained away by goblin metaphors or goblin analogies. Sometimes, the only thing that matters is acknowledging that the room feels empty because someone important is gone, and that emptiness is heavy.\n\nIf you're open to it, maybe we can just sit here for a bit. No goblins, no metaphors, just you and the quiet. You don't have to force yourself to get up right now. You don't have to explain why you're sad. Just breathe. The air is still there, even if it feels thin right now.",
